<DOC><DOCNO> AP881230-0141 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-30-88 1640EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Italy-Firecrackers     12-30 0148</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Italy-Firecrackers,0154</SECOND><HEAD>First Victim Of Year-End Mania</HEAD><DATELINE>CASERTA, Italy (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A New Year's firecracker killed a manFriday when the rocket he had made exploded, police said.   Police have seized large amounts of fireworks throughout Italy inan effort to prevent deaths and injuries.   Two towns in northern Italy, near Bergamo, have issued decreesbanning traditional year-end celebrations involving the explosives.   Police said most of the seized fireworks were from Japan andSouth Korea.   Rome police seized 440 pounds of imported firecrackers earlyFriday.   Authorities identified the man who was killed as Giovanni DeRosa, 28, of Casagiove, near Caserta in southern Italy. Theexplosion, outside his home damaged two parked cars and shatteredwindows.   Fireworks are part of Italians' traditional ways to send out theold year and usher in the new, along with throwing old furniturefrom windows and firing guns into the air.</TEXT></DOC>